<ul><li>Consider an object reaching the maixmum displacement&nbsp;\(\Delta t\)&nbsp;before the other one.</li><li>Their phase difference is a&nbsp;<b>fraction of a cycle</b>&nbsp;equal to&nbsp;\(\frac{\Delta t}{T}\)</li></ul><div>So the phase difference in radians is&nbsp;\(\frac{2\pi\Delta t}{T}\)</div>